  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Chef (Multi-Cuisine)",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking a skilled Multi-Cuisine Chef to prepare and execute a variety of dishes across Indian (North & South) and Western cuisines in a commercial kitchen environment. The successful candidate will be responsible for maintaining food quality, consistency, hygiene, and efficient kitchen operations.</p><p></p><p>Key Responsibilities</p><p>•\tPrepare and cook dishes from North Indian, South Indian, and Western cuisines</p><p>•\tHandle preparation of curries, gravies, tandoori items, fermented batters, and Western sauces</p><p>•\tCook items including (but not limited to):</p><p>•\tNorth Indian curries, kebabs, and breads</p><p>•\tSouth Indian dosa, idli, vada, chutneys, and sambar</p><p>•\tWestern pasta, grills, burgers, salads, and sauces</p><p>•\tPerform daily mise-en-place and ingredient preparation</p><p>•\tOperate kitchen equipment such as tandoor, tawa, grill, and ovens (where applicable)</p><p>•\tEnsure consistency in taste, portioning, and presentation</p><p>•\tMaintain cleanliness and comply with food safety and hygiene standards</p><p>•\tMinimise food wastage and assist with inventory control</p><p>•\tSupport peak-hour operations and coordinate with kitchen team</p><p>•\tAssist in menu development and training of junior kitchen staff when required</p><p></p><p>Requirements</p><p>•\tMinimum 4-5  years of relevant experience in a commercial kitchen</p><p>•\tExperience in multi-cuisine cooking preferred</p><p>•\tKnowledge of Indian spices, fermentation techniques, and Western cooking methods</p><p>•\tAbility to work in a fast-paced environment, including weekends and public holidays</p>",
